{"parse":{"title":"History of public transport authorities in Manchester","pageid":28074665,"revid":858497584,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>\n\nThe <b>history of public transport authorities in Manchester</b> details the various organisations that have been responsible for the public transport network in and around <a href=\"/wiki/Manchester\" title=\"Manchester\">Manchester</a>, England, since 1824.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Timeline\">Timeline</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=History_of_public_transport_authorities_in_Manchester&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Timeline\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>On 1 January 1824, the first horse bus service started by <a href=\"/wiki/John_Greenwood_(bus_operator)\" title=\"John Greenwood (bus operator)\">John Greenwood</a>, the proprietor of the <a href=\"/wiki/Pendleton,_Greater_Manchester\" title=\"Pendleton, Greater Manchester\">Pendleton</a> Toll Gates</li>\n<li>On 1 March 1865, the <a href=\"/wiki/Manchester_Carriage_Company\" title=\"Manchester Carriage Company\">Manchester Carriage Company</a> was formed which brought together a number of horse-bus operators in the Manchester area.</li>\n<li>In 1880 this became the <a href=\"/wiki/Manchester_Carriage_and_Tramways_Company\" title=\"Manchester Carriage and Tramways Company\">Manchester Carriage and Tramways Company</a> with some further consolidation, including the <a href=\"/wiki/Manchester_Suburban_Tramways_Company\" title=\"Manchester Suburban Tramways Company\">Manchester Suburban Tramways Company</a>.</li>\n<li>On 7 June 1901, <a href=\"/wiki/Manchester_Corporation_Tramways\" title=\"Manchester Corporation Tramways\"> Manchester Corporation Tramways Department</a> started electric tram operations, as the public operation. The former Carriage Company was wound up in 1903</li>\n<li>In 1929 the name was changed to  Manchester Corporation Transport Department to reflect the changing to motor buses</li>\n<li>In mid-1966 the name of this public operation was changed to Manchester City Transport.</li>\n<li>On 1 November 1969, control of Manchester City Transport and other surrounding council transport departments were transferred to South East Lancashire North East Cheshire Passenger Transport Executive (SELNEC PTE).<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>On 1 April 1974, SELNEC'S operating name became Greater Manchester Transport, and its coverage was expanded.</li>\n<li>During 1974 Greater Manchester Transport was rebranded as the <a href=\"/wiki/Greater_Manchester_Passenger_Transport_Executive\" title=\"Greater Manchester Passenger Transport Executive\">Greater Manchester Passenger Transport Executive</a> (GMPTE). This lasted until 2011.\n<ul><li>On 27 February 1986, Greater Manchester Transport's bus operation was transferred to a separate entity, Greater Manchester Buses Limited,<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> to comply with the <a href=\"/wiki/Transport_Act_1985\" title=\"Transport Act 1985\">Transport Act 1985</a>, adopting the <a href=\"/wiki/GM_Buses\" title=\"GM Buses\">GM Buses</a> trading name.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>On 13 December 1993, GM Buses was further split into GMB North<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and GMB South<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> on an approximate geographic basis. Just under four months later they were sold to <a href=\"/wiki/Management_buyout\" title=\"Management buyout\">employee buy out</a> teams.</li>\n<li>In February 1996, GMB South was sold to <a href=\"/wiki/Stagecoach_Group\" title=\"Stagecoach Group\">Stagecoach Group</a>,  becoming <a href=\"/wiki/Stagecoach_Manchester\" title=\"Stagecoach Manchester\">Stagecoach Manchester</a>.</li>\n<li>In March 1996, GMB North was sold to <a href=\"/wiki/FirstGroup\" title=\"FirstGroup\">First Bus</a>, eventually becoming <a href=\"/wiki/First_Greater_Manchester\" title=\"First Greater Manchester\">First Greater Manchester</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-TransportMuseum_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-TransportMuseum-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></li>\n<li>In April 2011. GMPTE became <a href=\"/wiki/Transport_for_Greater_Manchester\" title=\"Transport for Greater Manchester\">Transport for Greater Manchester</a> (TfGM).<sup id=\"cite_ref-TFGM_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-TFGM-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=History_of_public_transport_authorities_in_Manchester&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.selnec.org.uk/gmt_beyond.htm\">Greater Manchester Transport and beyond</a> Selnec Preservation Society</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://data.companieshouse.gov.uk/doc/company/01992869\">Companies House extract company no 1992869</a> Greater Manchester Buses Limited</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://archive.commercialmotor.com/article/26th-july-1986/18/11-tyne-and-wear-passenger-transport-executive-and\">Tyne &amp; Wear Passenger Transport Executive and Greater Manchesger</a> <i><a href=\"/wiki/Commercial_Motor\" title=\"Commercial Motor\">Commercial Motor</a></i> 26 July 1986</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://data.companieshouse.gov.uk/doc/company/02818607\">Companies House extract company no 2818607</a> First Manchester Limited formerly Greater Manchester Buses North Limited</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://data.companieshouse.gov.uk/doc/company/02818654\">Companies House extract company no 2818654</a> Greater Manchester Buses South Limited</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-TransportMuseum-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-TransportMuseum_6-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20101110051835/http://www.gmts.co.uk/explore/history/history.html\"><i>A Short History of Public Transport in Greater Manchester</i></a>, Greater Manchester Transport Society, archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.gmts.co.uk/explore/history/history.html\">the original</a> on 10 November 2010<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">, retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">18 July</span> 2010</span></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+Short+History+of+Public+Transport+in+Greater+Manchester&amp;rft.pub=Greater+Manchester+Transport+Society&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gmts.co.uk%2Fexplore%2Fhistory%2Fhistory.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHistory+of+public+transport+authorities+in+Manchester\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-TFGM-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-TFGM_7-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/local-news/all-change-greater-manchester-passenger-transport-857643\">\"All change: Greater Manchester Passenger Transport Executive becomes Transport for Greater Manchester \u2013 with a new logo of course\"</a>, <i>Manchester Evening News</i>, 11 January 2013<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">, retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">19 February</span> 2018</span></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Manchester+Evening+News&amp;rft.atitle=All+change%3A+Greater+Manchester+Passenger+Transport+Executive+becomes+Transport+for+Greater+Manchester+%E2%80%93+with+a+new+logo+of+course&amp;rft.date=2013-01-11&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.manchestereveningnews.co.uk%2Fnews%2Flocal-news%2Fall-change-greater-manchester-passenger-transport-857643&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHistory+of+public+transport+authorities+in+Manchester\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1239\nCached time: 20180907161535\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.080 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.113 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 464/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 7617/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 475/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansio